**Duplicate-name guard placed in second loop, after pipeline directive is assembled**

The empty-`Name` and unknown-`Position` guards are all in the first loop (fail-fast). The duplicate-`Name` guard lives in the second loop — meaning if two `MiddlewareSpec` entries share the same name and both have valid positions, the first loop completes successfully: both names are appended to `beforeFilters`/`afterFilters`, the pipeline directive is assembled with the name appearing twice (e.g. `"audit cors audit service_v3"`), and only then does the second loop return the error. The final result is still correct (`nil, error`), but the inconsistency makes the control flow harder to follow and a future contributor could add more first-loop processing while assuming duplicate detection has already happened.

Moving the `seen`-map initialisation and duplicate check into the first loop would make all validation uniform:

```go
seen := make(map[string]struct{}, len(spec.Middleware))
for _, mw := range spec.Middleware {
    if mw.Name == "" {
        return nil, fmt.Errorf("...")
    }
    if _, exists := seen[mw.Name]; exists {
        return nil, fmt.Errorf("duplicate middleware Name %q in pipeline %q", mw.Name, spec.PipelineName)
    }
    seen[mw.Name] = struct{}{}
    switch mw.Position {
    case types.PipelinePositionBefore:
        beforeFilters = append(beforeFilters, mw.Name)
    case types.PipelinePositionAfter:
        afterFilters = append(afterFilters, mw.Name)
    default:
        return nil, fmt.Errorf("...")
    }
}
```

